## Right Panel тАФ Node Classification (`_panel-right.tsx`)

Three booleans control which design sections are shown:

| Variable | Includes | Controls |
|---|---|---|
| `isContainer` | `Box`, `VStack`, `HStack`, `Center`, `Grid`, `GridItem`, `Card`, `Pressable`, `Checkbox`, `Radio`, `RadioGroup`, `Badge`, `Avatar`, `Fab`, `Skeleton`, `Alert`, `Link` | Alignment grid, Auto Layout section |
| `isTextNode` | `Text`, `Heading`, `ButtonText`, `BadgeText`, `AvatarFallbackText`, `CheckboxLabel`, `RadioLabel`, `FabLabel`, `SkeletonText`, `AlertText`, `LinkText` | Typography section |
| `isLeafWidget` | `Input`, `NavIcon`, `Image`, `NextImage`, `Textarea`, `Select`, `Slider`, `Progress`, `Spinner` | Hides Auto Layout + Alignment |

**Content section:** shown for `isTextNode` nodes (edits `node.text`) and for `isContainer` nodes that have a `Text` or `Heading` child (edits the first such child's `text`).

**Rule:** Any new component that the user should be able to layout children inside must be in `isContainer`. Text-only nodes that need font/color controls must be in `isTextNode`. Leaf widgets that have no layout children should be in `isLeafWidget`.

