## Critical Bug Fixes (Do Not Repeat)

### 1. Button disappears when any className is added

**Root cause:** `components/ui/button/index.tsx` used `hasCustomClassName(className)` тАФ any non-empty className (even `py-0 px-0` from padding) triggered `effectiveAction = 'custom'` тЖТ `bg-transparent`.

**Fix:** Only switch to `'custom'` action when className contains a `bg-*` token:
```tsx
const hasBg = useCustom && /\bbg-/.test(className!);
const effectiveAction = hasBg ? 'custom' : action;
```
**Rule:** Adding padding, margin, border-radius, opacity, or any non-color class to a Button must NOT override its background color.

---

### 2. Opacity uses inline `style.opacity`, never `opacity-N` class

**Root cause:** NativeWind does not compile dynamically applied `opacity-95`, `opacity-50` etc. (they're not in the source at build time).

**Fix:** Store opacity as `style.opacity` (decimal 0тАУ1). The slider `min=5` prevents accidental 0%. At 100%, `style.opacity` is removed entirely.

**Rule:** Never add `opacity-N` classes dynamically. Always use `patchStyle({ opacity: String(val/100) })`.

---

### 3. Rotation uses inline `style.transform`, never `rotate-[Ndeg]` class

**Root cause:** Same NativeWind dynamic class compilation issue.

**Fix:** Store rotation as `style.transform = rotate(Ndeg)`.

**Rule:** Never add `rotate-[...]` classes dynamically. Use `patchStyle({ transform: \`rotate(\${deg}deg)\` })`.

---

### 4. Colors use inline `style.backgroundColor / color / borderColor`

**Root cause:** NativeWind doesn't reliably compile arbitrary `bg-[#hex]` classes set dynamically at runtime.

**Fix:** All color picker changes use `patchStyle({ backgroundColor: hex })`, `patchStyle({ color: hex })`, `patchStyle({ borderColor: hex })`.

---

### 5. Flip H/V toggle-off didn't work (`\b` regex bug)

**Root cause:** `removeTwToken(cls, '-scale-x-')` generated regex `\b-scale-x-\S*`. The `\b` (word boundary) never fires before `-` (non-word char), so `-scale-x-100` could never be removed.

**Fix:** `removeTwToken` detects when prefix starts with a non-word char and uses `(?:^|\s)` boundary instead:
```ts
if (/^\w/.test(prefix)) {
  return className.replace(new RegExp(`\\b${escaped}\\S*`, 'g'), '')...
}
return className.replace(new RegExp(`(?:^|\\s)${escaped}\\S*`, 'g'), ' ')...
```
**Rule:** Any Tailwind utility starting with `-` (negated scale, negated rotate) requires the `(?:^|\s)` boundary, not `\b`.

---

### 6. Border radius: per-corner tokens vs global tokens

**Root cause:** The old `applyBorderRadius` emitted `rounded-lg rounded-none rounded-none rounded-none` (all global, last one wins тЖТ all corners = none). `expandBorderRadius` returned per-corner tokens like `rounded-tl-lg` which don't match any `ROUNDED_TOKENS` select option.

**Fix:**
- `expandBorderRadius`: parse per-corner tokens via regex `\brounded-tl(?:-\S+)?`, convert back to global format (`rounded-tl-lg` тЖТ `rounded-lg`) for select display.
- `applyBorderRadius`: when corners differ, emit per-corner tokens (`rounded-tl-lg rounded-tr-noneтАж`); when equal, emit single global token.
- Helper `globalToCornerToken('rounded-lg', 'tl')` тЖТ `'rounded-tl-lg'`.

**Rule:** Never concatenate four global `rounded-*` tokens for mixed corners. Always convert to `rounded-{corner}-{size}`.

---

### 7. CONTAINER_TYPES Must Stay in Sync Across Three Files

**Root cause:** `CONTAINER_TYPES` in `_canvas.tsx` and `LAYER_CONTAINER_TYPES` in `_panel-left.tsx` only contained 8 types (`Box`, `VStack`, `HStack`, `ScrollView`, `View`, `Card`, `SafeAreaView`, `Pressable`). Any type NOT in this set is treated as a leaf тАФ you cannot drop children into it when it's empty (the `children.length > 0` fallback only helps non-empty containers).

**Impact:** `Center`, `Grid`, `GridItem`, and all Gluestack compound containers were non-droppable when first placed on the canvas.

**Fix:** All three sets must include the **same container types**:
- `_canvas.tsx` тЖТ `CONTAINER_TYPES` (controls drag-over hit logic)
- `_panel-left.tsx` тЖТ `LAYER_CONTAINER_TYPES` (controls layers-panel expand icon)
- `_panel-right.tsx` тЖТ `isContainer` array (controls Auto Layout design panel section)

**Rule:** Whenever you add a new container component to the palette, add its `type` string to all three locations. The canonical list is in `_panel-right.tsx`'s `isContainer` array.

---

### 8. defaultNode className Must Include All Implicit Style Tokens

**Root cause:** The right panel reads layout/alignment tokens (`flex-row`, `flex-col`, `items-*`, `justify-*`) exclusively from `props.className`. Gluestack compound components (Center, VStack, HStack, etc.) apply these tokens internally via their `tva` base styles тАФ NOT from `props.className`. So when a component is freshly dropped, the panel shows no direction selected and no alignment cell highlighted even though the component visually centers/stacks correctly.

**Fix:** Always include all layout-defining tokens explicitly in `defaultNode.props.className`:
- `Center` тЖТ `flex flex-col items-center justify-center`
- `VStack` тЖТ `flex flex-col`
- `HStack` тЖТ `flex flex-row`
- Any other container with an implicit flex direction or alignment тЖТ add those tokens to `className`

**Rule:** If a component has implicit `flex-*`, `items-*`, or `justify-*` built into its component style, mirror those tokens in `defaultNode.className` so the right panel reflects the actual visual behavior immediately on drop.

---

### 9. Padding / Margin / Gap тАФ exact pixel values via inline style

**Root cause:** Using Tailwind spacing scale (`pxToSpacingScale`) forced values to snap to 2px increments. Input `1` тЖТ rounded to `0` тЖТ no margin. Input `3` тЖТ `mx-0.5` (not compiled in older safelist).

**Fix:** All three use `patchStyle` with direct CSS properties:
- Padding: `style.paddingLeft/Right/Top/Bottom`
- Margin: `style.marginLeft/Right/Top/Bottom`
- Gap: `style.gap`

**Rule:** Never use `patchCls(applyPadding/applyMargin/pxToTw)` for user-entered spacing values in the builder. Use `patchStyle` with exact `px` strings so any value the user types is applied exactly.

---

### 8. `pxToSpacingScale` ties round UP

When a px value is equally distant between two scale values (e.g. `1` ties between `0` and `2`), round UP:
```ts
.reduce((a, b) => Math.abs(b - px) <= Math.abs(a - px) ? b : a);
```
Previously used `<` which always rounded down тЖТ `1` тЖТ `0` тЖТ no spacing.

---

## `_tw-utils.ts` тАФ Key Utilities

### `removeTwToken(className, prefix)`
Removes all tokens matching prefix. Uses `\b` for word-char prefixes (`p-`, `gap-`, `rounded-`). Uses `(?:^|\s)` for non-word-char prefixes (`-scale-x-`, `-rotate-`).

### `replaceTwToken(className, prefix, newToken)`
Replaces the first matching token, or appends if none found. Uses `(?:^|\s)` boundary with space-preserving replacement.

### `parseTwToken(className, prefix)`
Returns the first token matching `\b{prefix}\S*`, or `null`.

### `expandPadding / expandBorderRadius / expandMargin`
Parse className into structured px/token values for display in inputs. These are ONLY used for reading initial values (display). Writing always uses `patchStyle`.

### `applyAlignment(className, cellIdx)`
Maps 0тАУ8 cell index тЖТ `items-*` + `justify-*` classes. Used by the 9-cell grid.

### `globalToCornerToken(global, corner)`
`'rounded-lg'` + `'tl'` тЖТ `'rounded-tl-lg'`. Used in `applyBorderRadius` for mixed-corner case.

---

## Tailwind Safelist (`tailwind.config.js`)

All dynamically applied builder classes must be in the safelist. Current coverage:
- Spacing: `p/px/py/pt/pr/pb/pl-{scale}` (includes decimals like `1.5`)
- Margin: `m/mx/my/mt/mr/mb/ml-{scale|auto}` (includes decimals)
- Gap, W, H, max-w, opacity, rounded, text-*, font-*, leading, tracking
- Flex: direction, items, justify, wrap
- Rotate (including negated and arbitrary): `-?rotate-(N|[...])`, `-?scale-x/y-*`
- Position: `static/relative/absolute/fixed/sticky`
- Z-index: `z-0/10/20/30/40/50/auto`
- Cursor, display, overflow, text-align, text-decoration, text-transform, self-*

**Rule:** Any new class dynamically applied by the builder must be added to the safelist OR stored as an inline style property.

