### 19. Drop indicator direction тАФ vertical for row containers

**Root cause:** The drop indicator (blue line) was always rendered horizontally (`dropLineY` only), even when dragging over a horizontal container (`HStack` or `Box flex-row`). Users saw the insertion cue in the wrong axis.

**Fix:**
1. `isRowContainer(node)` helper in `_canvas.tsx` тАФ returns `true` for `HStack` type OR any node whose `className` contains `flex-row`.
2. `nearestGapH(clientX, container, children)` тАФ mirrors `nearestGap()` but calculates insertion position along the X axis (returns `lineX`).
3. `dropLineX` state in `_canvas.tsx` тАФ holds the horizontal pixel position for the vertical indicator line.
4. `onDragOver` now calls `nearestGapH + setDropLineX` for row containers and `nearestGap + setDropLineY` for column containers. Both states are always reset together (only one is active at a time).
5. `DropZoneLine` in `_overlay.tsx` accepts both `x` (vertical line) and `y` (horizontal line). When `x` is set, renders a `2px ├Ч height` vertical bar; when `y` is set, renders a `width ├Ч 2px` horizontal bar.

**Tests:** `DI-01`тАУ`DI-04` in `test-dnd.spec.ts`.

**Rule:** Any container whose `type === 'HStack'` or whose `className` contains `flex-row` is a row container тАФ the insertion indicator must be vertical. All other containers use the existing horizontal line.

---

### 13. Hug / Fill does nothing when node was previously resized

**Root cause:** Clicking Hug (`w-fit`) or Fill (`w-full`) only patched `className`. But if the node was resized via drag handles or the W/H number input, it has `style.width: "100px"` as an inline style. Inline styles have higher CSS specificity than any class, so `w-full` / `w-fit` were silently ignored.

**Fix:** Hug and Fill click handlers now call `patchStyle({ width: '', minWidth: '' })` (or `height/minHeight`) in addition to updating the className. Fixed mode intentionally does NOT clear the inline style тАФ it preserves the user's explicit size.

**Rule:** Any time you add a layout-mode class (`w-fit`, `w-full`, `h-fit`, `h-full`) you must also clear the corresponding inline style property. Otherwise the inline style wins.

