### 14. Drag ghost: original element visible during drag (double-image)

**Root cause:** When dragging a non-absolute node, the browser shows a ghost copy following the cursor AND the original element stays fully opaque in place тАФ creating a duplicate.

**Fix:** In `onDragStart` (non-absolute path), one `requestAnimationFrame` after calling `setDragImage` (so the ghost snapshot is captured at full opacity), set `nodeEl.style.opacity = '0.3'` for all dragged elements and store them in `draggedElRef = useRef<HTMLElement[]>([])`. Restore in both `onDrop` and `onDragEnd` by iterating `draggedElRef.current`.

**Key subtlety тАФ `onDrop` clears the ref first:** `onDrop` sets `draggingNodeIdRef.current = null` before `onDragEnd` fires. So `onDragEnd` cannot query by node ID to restore opacity. Fix: use a dedicated `draggedElRef` (array of DOM elements) that is independent of `draggingNodeIdRef`. Both `onDrop` and `onDragEnd` clear it тАФ whichever fires first wins, the second is a no-op.

**Rule:** Never restore drag opacity via `draggingNodeIdRef` тАФ that ref is cleared in `onDrop` before `onDragEnd` fires. Always use `draggedElRef` (the actual DOM elements captured at drag-start).

**Ghost size inflation (canvas zoom) + composite ghost for multi-drag:**

`setDragImage(nodeEl, ox, oy)` where `nodeEl` is inside a `transform: scale(zoom)` container captures the element at its SCREEN size (= CSS size ├Ч zoom). At zoom > 1 the ghost is inflated.

Fix: build a ghost `div` appended to `document.body` (outside the scaled canvas) from clones of all dragged elements, positioned at their relative screen-space positions divided by `zoom`:

```ts
const rects = allDragIds.map(id => ({
  el:   document.querySelector(`[data-builder-id="${id}"]`) as HTMLElement,
  rect: document.querySelector(`[data-builder-id="${id}"]`)?.getBoundingClientRect(),
})).filter(r => r.el && r.rect);

const minX = Math.min(...rects.map(r => r.rect.left));
const minY = Math.min(...rects.map(r => r.rect.top));

const ghostEl = document.createElement('div');
ghostEl.style.cssText = `position:fixed;left:-9999px;top:-9999px;pointer-events:none;width:${(maxX-minX)/zoom}px;height:${(maxY-minY)/zoom}px;`;
document.body.appendChild(ghostEl);

for (const { el, rect } of rects) {
  const clone = el.cloneNode(true) as HTMLElement;
  clone.style.position = 'absolute';
  clone.style.left  = `${(rect.left - minX) / zoom}px`;
  clone.style.top   = `${(rect.top  - minY) / zoom}px`;
  clone.style.width  = `${rect.width  / zoom}px`;
  clone.style.height = `${rect.height / zoom}px`;
  clone.style.transform = '';
  ghostEl.appendChild(clone);
}

e.dataTransfer.setDragImage(ghostEl, (e.clientX - minX) / zoom, (e.clientY - minY) / zoom);
requestAnimationFrame(() => { document.body.removeChild(ghostEl); /* then fade originals */ });
```

**Rules:**
- Always divide screen coordinates by `zoom` when building a ghost that lives outside the canvas.
- For multi-drag, always build the composite ghost from ALL `allDragIds`, not just the primary node тАФ this shows all selected elements moving together (Figma-style).

