### 18. Stale marquee-select after drag from empty canvas space

**Root cause:** `onPointerDown` (canvas background) sets `marqueeStartRef.current` whenever a click lands on empty canvas (no node under cursor). When you then drag nodes that are already selected (via the `selectedIds` fallback in `onDragStart`), the HTML5 drag takes over and the browser stops firing pointer events тАФ so `onPointerUp` (which normally clears `marqueeStartRef`) **never fires**. On the next mouse-move the engine still thinks a marquee is active and draws the selection rectangle.

**Fix:**
1. `onDragStart` тАФ at the very top, clear `marqueeStartRef.current` and call `setMarquee(null)`.
2. `onDragEnd` тАФ clear them again as a safety net.

```ts
// onDragStart (first lines):
if (marqueeStartRef.current) {
  marqueeStartRef.current = null;
  setMarquee(null);
}
```

**Rule:** Any code path that transitions from pointer-down тЖТ HTML5 drag must clear `marqueeStartRef` immediately in `onDragStart`, because the browser eats the `pointerup` event that would normally do the cleanup.

---

### 16. Multi-select drag: clicking a selected node deselects others before drag starts

**Root cause:** The capture overlay's `onPointerDown` called `select(hit.id, e.shiftKey)` unconditionally. Without shift, this replaced the entire multi-selection with just the clicked node тАФ so by the time `onDragStart` fired, `selectedIds` only ever had one entry.

**Fix:** Guard in `onPointerDown`:
```tsx
if (hit.kind === 'node') {
  const { selectedIds: curIds } = useBuilderStore.getState();
  // Only change selection if the node isn't already selected (or shift is held).
  // Preserve multi-selection for drag; onPointerUp reduces it if no drag occurred.
  if (!curIds.includes(hit.id) || e.shiftKey) {
    select(hit.id, e.shiftKey);
  }
}
```
`onPointerUp` already handles reducing multi-selection to single on a plain click with no drag.

**Rule:** `onPointerDown` on the capture overlay must NEVER replace an existing multi-selection when the clicked node is already selected without shift тАФ doing so destroys multi-select drag before it starts.

---

### 17. Multi-select drag: only one node moves on drop

**Root cause:** `onDrop` always called `moveNode(singleId, ...)` тАФ no path for moving multiple selected nodes.

**Fix:**
1. Added `moveNodes(nodeIds[], newParentId, atIdx)` to `_store.ts` тАФ removes all specified nodes in one pass, then inserts them consecutively at the target. Adjusts `atIdx` by counting how many of the moved nodes were already before the target index in the destination parent.
2. In `onDragStart`, computed `allDragIds = selectedIds.includes(dragId) && selectedIds.length > 1 ? [...selectedIds] : [dragId]` and stored it in `multiDragIdsRef`.
3. In `onDrop`, when `multiDragIdsRef.current.length > 1`, call `moveNodes(allIds, ...)` instead of `moveNode`.
4. All nodes in `allDragIds` are faded (opacity 0.3) during drag; all are restored on `onDrop`/`onDragEnd`.

**Rule:** Any drag-and-drop operation that could involve multiple selected nodes must use `moveNodes` (not repeated `moveNode` calls). Repeated single moves cause index drift and incorrect ordering.

**Additional guard тАФ topmost-only filter:** `moveNodes` must filter `nodeIds` to only the topmost nodes before moving. If a marquee-selection includes both a parent (e.g. `Button`) and its child (e.g. `ButtonText`), naively moving both independently inserts `ButtonText` as a sibling of `Button` тАФ outside Gluestack's Button context тАФ causing a hard crash (`useStyleContext` returns undefined). Fix: before collecting `nodesToMove`, walk each node's ancestor chain; if any ancestor is also in the move set, skip that node (it will ride along inside its ancestor's cloned subtree).

```typescript
const nodeIdSet = new Set(nodeIds);
const topMostIds = nodeIds.filter(id => {
  let parent = findParentNode(s.pageNodes, id);
  while (parent !== null && parent !== undefined) {
    if (nodeIdSet.has(parent.id ?? '')) return false; // ancestor also moving
    parent = findParentNode(s.pageNodes, parent.id ?? '');
  }
  return true;
});
// use topMostIds instead of nodeIds for nodesToMove
```

