**┬з26 Absolute Node + Multi-Select Drag**

**Root cause:** The absolute-positioning path in `onDragOver` / `onDrop` checked only the PRIMARY dragged node's `className` for `absolute`. When the user had multiple nodes selected (including an absolute one) and dragged, the code entered the absolute path and moved ONLY that one node; all other selected nodes stayed in place.

**Fix:** Guard the absolute path with `earlyAllDraggingIds.length <= 1`:
```typescript
if (isAbsPos && earlyAllDraggingIds.length <= 1) {
  // single absolute node: free-form reposition
  ...
  return;
}
// Multi-drag: fall through to flow-drop path so all selected nodes move together
```
Same guard in `onDrop`: `if (isAbsNode && !isMultiDrag)`.

**Rule:** The absolute-positioning path must never activate during multi-drag. All nodes in a multi-selection must move as a flow group.

