## ┬з29 ButtonText Crash Guard тАФ REQUIRED_PARENT + ALLOWED_CHILDREN

**Root cause:** `ButtonText` uses `useStyleContext(SCOPE)` to read `variant/size/action` from its parent `Button`. Moving it outside a `Button` (via canvas DnD, layers DnD, or context menu) makes that context `undefined` тЖТ hard crash.

**Fix:** `moveNode` in `_store.ts` validates both directions before any tree mutation:
```typescript
// Node requires a specific parent type
const REQUIRED_PARENT: Record<string, string> = { ButtonText: 'Button' };
if (REQUIRED_PARENT[node.type]) {
  const newParent = newParentId ? findNode(s.pageNodes, newParentId) : null;
  if (!newParent || newParent.type !== REQUIRED_PARENT[node.type]) return s;
}
// Parent only accepts specific child types
const ALLOWED: Record<string, Set<string>> = { Button: new Set(['ButtonText', 'NavIcon']) };
if (newParentId) {
  const newParent = findNode(s.pageNodes, newParentId);
  if (newParent && ALLOWED[newParent.type] && !ALLOWED[newParent.type].has(node.type)) return s;
}
```

**Rule:** Any time you add a Gluestack compound component (like `CheckboxIndicator`, `RadioIndicator`, etc.) that uses `useStyleContext`, add it to `REQUIRED_PARENT` and the parent type to `ALLOWED` in `_store.ts`. The crash will occur even in the live preview тАФ the guard must be in the store, not just the UI.

