## E2E Tests тАФ Known Patterns and Pitfalls

### Color Inputs: Write to BOTH className and style

**Problem:** Text color and stroke (border) color pickers write to `className` as Tailwind arbitrary classes (`text-[hex]`, `border-[hex]`). Tests that check `style.color` or `style.borderColor` will fail.

**Fix:** Always write to BOTH when handling color changes:
```tsx
// Stroke color (input-stroke-color)
onChange={hex => {
  const cleaned = cls.replace(/\bborder-\[[^\]]+\]/g, '').replace(/\s+/g, ' ').trim();
  patchCls(hex ? `${cleaned} border-[${hex}]`.trim() : cleaned);
  patchStyle({ borderColor: hex || '' });   // also update inline style
}}

// Text color (input-text-color)
onChange={hex => {
  const cleaned = cls.replace(/\btext-\[[^\]]+\]/g, '').replace(/\s+/g, ' ').trim();
  patchCls(hex ? `${cleaned} text-[${hex}]`.trim() : cleaned);
  patchStyle({ color: hex || '' });   // also update inline style
}}
```

---

### Gap Mode тЗФ Button: Use data-testid, Not getByText

**Problem:** For Box nodes, there are THREE `тЗФ` icons in the right panel: (1) `self-stretch` in Self Alignment, (2) `Flip H` in Transform, (3) `Space-between` in Auto Layout Gap Mode. Using `getByText('тЗФ').nth(1)` hits Flip H, not Gap Mode.

**Fix:** The Gap Mode space-between button has `data-testid="gap-mode-space-between"`. Always use it:
```typescript
await page.locator('[data-testid="gap-mode-space-between"]').click();
```

---

### Alignment / Gap: Requires Container Node in Tests

**Problem:** Auto Layout (Gap) and Alignment sections only render when `showLayout = true` (container nodes). Tests that drop a `Button` and then look for `input-gap` or `alignment-cell` will time out because these elements don't render for leaf widgets.

**Fix:** Drop a `Box` (or `VStack`/`HStack`) when testing alignment or gap:
```typescript
await dropComponent(page, 'Box');   // NOT 'Button'
await selectFirstRootNodeViaLayers(page);
// Now alignment-cell and input-gap are visible
```

---

### Drag From Left Panel Into Container: Use dispatchEvent

**Problem:** `dragTo(containerEl)` fails when targeting an element inside the canvas page frame because the transparent capture overlay (`data-builder-overlay="capture"`) intercepts Playwright's synthetic mouse events, preventing the drop from landing.

**Fix:** Use `dispatchEvent` to fire HTML5 DnD events directly on the canvas. The canvas `onDrop` handler reads `text/primitive-node` from `dataTransfer`:
```typescript
const containerBox = await page.locator('[data-builder-id="my-box"]').boundingBox();
const cx = containerBox.x + containerBox.width / 2;
const cy = containerBox.y + containerBox.height / 2;

await page.evaluate(async ({ cx, cy, primitiveStr }) => {
  const canvas = document.querySelector('[data-testid="builder-canvas"]') as HTMLElement;
  const dt = new DataTransfer();
  dt.items.add(primitiveStr, 'text/primitive-node');
  canvas?.dispatchEvent(new DragEvent('dragover', { bubbles: true, cancelable: true, dataTransfer: dt, clientX: cx, clientY: cy }));
  await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 150));  // let dragover settle the dropTargetRef
  canvas?.dispatchEvent(new DragEvent('drop', { bubbles: true, cancelable: true, dataTransfer: dt, clientX: cx, clientY: cy }));
}, { cx, cy, primitiveStr: JSON.stringify(primitiveNode) });
```

**Note:** `dragTo(frame)` (targeting the whole page frame) still works for dropping at root level тАФ only targeting specific elements inside the frame fails.

---

### Padding Inputs Write to Style, Not className

**Rule:** Individual padding inputs (`input-pad-top`, `input-pad-right`, etc.) write to `props.style` via `patchStyle`. Tests must check `style.paddingTop` etc., not `className`.

**Exception:** `input-pad-h` (combined H padding) also writes `px-[${px}px]` to `className` (for the BP-35 regression test: verifying Button background stays non-transparent when className is set).

---

### Flaky dropButton / dropComponent: Increase Retries

**Problem:** When running 280 tests with 5 workers, `dropButton` and `dropComponent` occasionally time out on `waitFor('[data-builder-id]')` due to resource contention.

**Fix:** `dropButton` in `button-panel.spec.ts` retries up to 5 times with a 300ms wait between retries. Similarly, always run the full suite with `--retries=1` in CI to handle environment-level flakiness gracefully.
